## The Problem

India's credit system has a brutal catch-22 at its heart:

> *You can't get a loan because you have no credit history.*  
> *You have no credit history because you've never gotten a loan.*

**CIBIL** — India's primary credit bureau — only scores people who've already used bank products. Credit cards. Home loans. Car EMIs. But what about the people who never needed those, or were never given access?

| Who gets left out | Scale |
|---|---|
| Gig workers (Zomato, Swiggy, Ola, Uber) | 15M+ |
| Freelancers & self-employed | 400M+ |
| Small business owners & shopkeepers | 63M MSMEs |
| First-generation urban migrants | 100M+ |
| Farmers & rural workers | 120M+ |

These people are not irresponsible. They are simply **invisible** to a system not designed for them.

---

## The Solution

**NeuroCredit** is a three-layer alternative credit scoring platform:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                         │
│   User submits 14 financial signals (UPI, bills, etc)  │
│                         │                               │
│                         ▼                               │
│          ┌──────────────────────────┐                   │
│          │    FastAPI Backend       │                    │
│          │  (orchestration layer)   │                    │
│          └────────────┬─────────────┘                   │
│                       │                                  │
│           ┌───────────┴───────────┐                     │
│           │                       │                     │
│           ▼                       ▼                     │
│   ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────────────┐        │
│   │  ML Model    │     │  Polygon Blockchain   │        │
│   │  (GBR/XGB)   │────▶│  NeuroCredit.sol      │        │
│   │  score 300–900│    │  ERC-5484 SBT         │        │
│   └──────────────┘     └──────────┬───────────┘        │
│                                   │                     │
│                         ┌─────────▼──────────┐         │
│                         │  Soul Bound Token   │         │
│                         │  (in user's wallet) │         │
│                         └─────────┬──────────┘         │
│                                   │                     │
│                    Lender calls verifyCredit()          │
│                    ← score + eligibility only           │
│                    ← zero personal data exposed         │
│                                                         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Layer 1 · AI Credit Scoring
A Gradient Boosting ML model processes 14 alternative financial signals and outputs a score from **300 to 900** — the same range as CIBIL, so every lender already knows how to read it.

### Layer 2 · Blockchain Ownership
The score is minted as a **non-transferable ERC-5484 Soul Bound Token** on Polygon. You own it. Not us. Not a bank. It lives in your wallet forever.

### Layer 3 · Privacy-Preserving Verification
Lenders call one public function on the smart contract. They get: score, grade, eligibility. **Nothing else.** Your raw data is never on-chain.

---

## How it Works

### The 14 Signals

NeuroCredit scores people on what they actually **do** with money:

```
Payment History (35% weight)
├── Utility bills paid on time          [0.0 – 1.0]
├── Mobile bill paid on time            [0.0 – 1.0]
└── Rent paid on time                   [0.0 – 1.0]

Transaction Activity (25% weight)
├── Monthly UPI transaction count       [0 – 500]
├── Average transaction amount (₹)     [any]
└── Transaction consistency             [0.0 – 1.0]

Income Stability (20% weight)
├── Number of income sources            [1 – 10]
├── Estimated monthly income (₹)       [any]
├── Income volatility                   [0.0=stable – 1.0=volatile]
└── Employment type                     [0=gig, 1=self-employed, 2=salaried]

Savings Behaviour (10% weight)
├── Savings rate                        [0.0 – 0.6]
└── Has recurring SIP / investment      [0 or 1]

Tenure & Stability (10% weight)
├── Mobile number tenure (months)       [0 – 240]
└── Same address duration (months)      [0 – 240]
```

### Score Grades

| Score | Grade | Risk | Eligible |
|---|---|---|---|
| 800 – 900 | ⭐ Excellent | Very Low | ✅ Yes |
| 720 – 799 | ✅ Good | Low | ✅ Yes |
| 650 – 719 | 🟡 Fair | Medium | ✅ Yes |
| 580 – 649 | 🟠 Poor | High | ❌ No |
| 300 – 579 | 🔴 Very Poor | Very High | ❌ No |

### Model Performance

The Gradient Boosting Regressor (equivalent to XGBoost) was trained on 5,000 synthetic profiles:

```
Mean Absolute Error (MAE) : 13.2 points
R² Score                  : 0.84
Training profiles         : 5,000
Test split                : 20%
Score range               : 300 – 900
```

An MAE of 13.2 on a 600-point range = **2.2% average error**.

