## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.10+
- Node.js 18+ (for contract deployment only)
- A Polygon wallet (MetaMask) for the full blockchain flow

### 1 · Clone & Install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/neurocredit.git
cd neurocredit

pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 2 · Train the ML Model

```bash
python ml/train.py
```

Expected output:
```
Generating 5,000 synthetic training profiles...
Score range: 539 to 833
Training GradientBoosting model (300 estimators)...
MAE: 13.22 | R2: 0.8387
Model + artifacts saved!
```

The trained model is saved to `ml/artifacts/`. **Pre-trained artifacts are included in the repo**, so you can skip this step and go straight to the backend.

### 3 · Start the Backend

```bash
cd backend
python main.py
```

```
INFO:     Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8000
INFO:     Application startup complete.
```

Interactive API docs available at: `http://localhost:8000/docs`

### 4 · Open the Frontend

```bash
# No build step. Just open directly:
open frontend/index.html

# Or serve locally:
python -m http.server 3000
# then visit http://localhost:3000/frontend/
```

The frontend has a **full offline fallback** — the scoring engine is mirrored in JavaScript, so every feature works even without the Python backend running.

### 5 · Deploy the Smart Contract (optional)

```bash
npm install --save-dev hardhat @nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox

# Add to hardhat.config.js:
# networks: { 'polygon-amoy': { url: process.env.RPC_URL, accounts: [process.env.PRIVATE_KEY] } }

npx hardhat compile
npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.js --network polygon-amoy
```

Get free MATIC for Polygon Amoy testnet: https://faucet.polygon.technology

